I bought this for my little sister.  She loves Jem and I was so glad to be able to find it for her on amazon.  She never gets tired of watching it and sometimes I watch it with her.  I think the themes of the shows never go out of style.  It's a real classic for kids of all ages.  It's such a fun dvd.

I absolutely love this DVD! I was a big fan of the cartoon and was overly excited when I found out that it was being released on DVD! Even though I only have the first season, I'm perfectly content with it. The only thing is I wish it would've included some of the extra features like season three does. Perfectly priced and I love it! Thumbs up!!

...THAT is the Question! Let me begin by admitting that my own personal answer was NO - I do NOT own this set, nor do I see ANY reason to do so. Not that there's inherently anything wrong with it, and there's certainly nothing wrong with Jem, the 1980's cartoon about the girl singer with the "double life". The problem with this particular set lies in its perceived value as a PRODUCT: it contains only the so-called Season One, 26 episodes out of the total 65. Any true fan of Jem should instead buy Jem and the Holograms: The Truly Outrageous Complete Series, especially as that seems the ONLY way to get the extra disc containing all the bonus material like the Jem Bible on CD-ROM and interviews with cast members, creators, and fans. If you're not already familiar with Jem and think of buying this to find out if you like it or not, consider that if the answer is YES, you are automatically locked into getting the 2 additional sets that omit the bonus material altogether. This is probably a nice set by itself - but not worth buying in the long run, especially if you're already a fan of Jem.

As a guy I souldn't admit I watched this growing up. I did ,however, and liked it a whole lot. The music fit the time and Jem felt like a superheroine to me. Those hologram powers kept this comic book lover glued to the screen. I believe marvel had a hand in this.

If you are a nostalgic nut like I am you will love this series. I used to watch Jem as a child with my cousin and younger sister and this transported me backed to the 80's and my 4-5year old self wanting to be a Jem girl. Yes as an adult parts of this is corny, but its the nostalgic element attached that has me loving it. Jem was to us back then what Miami Vice was to the older persons in this era.
